conventional LLM, reasoning LLM (or reasoning model), and an LLM wrapped in=
 an agent harness.</em></figcaption></figure></div><p>In other words, the a=
gent is the system that repeatedly calls the model inside an environment.</=
p><p>So, in short, we can summarize it like this:</p><ul><li><p><em>LLM:</e=
m><span> the raw model</span></p></li><li><p><em>Reasoning model</em><span>=
: an LLM optimized to output intermediate reasoning traces and to verify it=
self more</span></p></li><li><p><em>Agent:</em><span> a loop that uses a mo=
del plus tools, memory, and environment feedback</span></p></li><li><p><em>=
Agent harness:</em><span> the software scaffold around an agent that manage=
s context, tool use, prompts, state, and control flow</span></p></li><li><p=
><em>Coding harness:</em><span> a special case of an agent harness; i.e., a=
 task-specific harness for software engineering that manages code context, =
tools, execution, and iterative feedback</span></p></li></ul><p><span>As li=
sted above, in the context of agents and coding tools, we also have the two=
 popular terms </span><em>agent harness</em><span> and (agentic) </span><em=
>coding harness</em><span>. A coding harness is the software scaffold aroun=
d a model that helps it write and edit code effectively. And an agent harne=
ss is a bit broader and not specific to coding (e.g., think of OpenClaw). C=
odex and Claude Code can be considered coding harnesses.</span></p><p>Anywa=
ys, A better LLM provides a better foundation for a reasoning model (which =
involves additional training), and a harness gets more out of this reasonin=
g model.</p><p>Sure, LLMs and reasoning models are also capable of solving =
coding tasks by themselves (without a harness), but coding work is only par=
tly about next-token generation. A lot of it is about repo navigation, sear=
ch, function lookup, diff application, test execution, error inspection, an=
d keeping all the relevant information in context. (Coders may know that th=
is is hard mental work, which is why we don=E2=80=99t like to be disrupted =
during coding sessions :)).</p><div class=3D"captioned-image-container"><fi=
